==现状==
2007年2月28日，西班牙[[巴利阿里群島|巴利阿里群島]]議會通過了世界上第一個承認所有類人猿擁有合法[[人格|人格]]的立法。<ref name="Rose">{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/viewpoint/vp_rose/20070802.html |title=Going ape over human rights |accessdate=2008-06-26 |author=Thomas Rose |date=2007-08-02 |publisher=CBC News |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100203225450/http://www.cbc.ca/news/viewpoint/vp_rose/20070802.html |archivedate=2010-02-03 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 該立法引起了整個西班牙的反響。2008年6月25日，一個議會委員會開始催促西班牙政府保障靈長類動物有生命權和自由權，如果能過成功，那麼“將通過西班牙刑法典禁止有害的靈長類[[動物實驗|動物實驗]]以及馬戲團豢養、商業廣告或非法拍攝”。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/scienceNews/idUSL256586320080625 |title=Spanish parliament to extend rights to apes |accessdate=2008-07-11 |date=2008-06-25 |publisher=Reuters |archive-date=2021-04-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210424191930/https://www.reuters.com/article/scienceNews/idUSL256586320080625 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

歐洲在動物權利立法上也已做過努力。1992年，瑞士修改了其[[瑞士憲法|憲法]]，承認動物是“生命”而不是“東西”。<ref name="APBerlin">{{cite web |url=http://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2002/05/18/germany-rights.htm |title=Germany guarantees animal rights in constitution |accessdate=2008-06-26 |date=2002-05-18 |publisher=Associated Press |archive-date=2009-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090923214001/http://www.usatoday.com/news/world/2002/05/18/germany-rights.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref> 不過1999年瑞士憲法被重寫，這個修正案就失效了。2002年德國在憲法修正案中再次確保動物權利，成為第一個承認動物權利的[[歐盟|歐盟]]國家。<ref name="APBerlin" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/europe/06/21/germany.animals/index.html |title=Germany guarantees animal rights |accessdate=2008-06-26 |date=2002-06-21 |publisher=CNN |archive-date=2013-10-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019042639/http://edition.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/europe/06/21/germany.animals/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2002/jun/22/germany.animalwelfarel |title=German animals given legal rights |accessdate=2008-06-26 |date=2002-06-22 |author=Kate Connolly |publisher=The Guardian |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150521131353/http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2002/jun/22/germany.animalwelfarel |archivedate=2015-05-21}}</ref>

1999年，五大人科物种在[[新西兰|新西兰]]获得了有力的保护，禁止其被當做研究、试验的目標。有人认为，新西兰的保护额度到了一种弱的[[自然权利|法律权利]]。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.animallaw.info/journals/jo_pdf/lralvol_7p35.pdf |title="A STEP AT A TIME: NEW ZEALAND'S PROGRESS TOWARD HOMINID RIGHTS" BY ROWAN TAYLOR |accessdate=2013-07-07 |archive-date=2013-07-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130728153305/http://www.animallaw.info/journals/jo_pdf/lralvol_7p35.pdf |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

一些欧洲国家（包括奥地利、荷兰和瑞典）完全禁止在动物实验方面使用类人猿。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.parlament.gv.at/PAKT/VHG/XXII/I/I_00993/fnameorig_043770.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2015-11-24 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303200904/http://www.parlament.gv.at/PAKT/VHG/XXII/I/I_00993/fnameorig_043770.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2014年末，[[阿根廷|阿根廷]]通过了给予圈养猩猩基本人权的法律。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/12/23/world/americas/feat-orangutan-rights-ruling/|title=Argentine orangutan granted unprecedented legal rights|last1=Giménez|first1=Emiliano|last2=|first2=|date=January 4, 2015|website=edition.cnn.com|publisher=[[抽象化|CNN Espanol]]|access-date=April 21, 2015|archive-date=2021-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210403030759/https://edition.cnn.com/2014/12/23/world/americas/feat-orangutan-rights-ruling/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2015年4月20日，纽约州最高法院的巴巴拉法官先生签署针对两只圈养的猩猩的[[人身保護令|保护令]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nonhumanrightsproject.org/2015/04/20/judge-recognizes-two-chimpanzees-as-legal-persons-grants-them-writ-of-habeas-corpus/ |title=Judge Recognizes Two Chimpanzees as Legal Persons, Grants them Writ of Habeas Corpus |author= |date=April 20, 2015 |website=nonhumanrightsproject.org |publisher=[[Nonhuman_Rights_Project|Nonhuman Rights Project]] |access-date=April 21, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160909212513/http://www.nonhumanrightsproject.org/2015/04/20/judge-recognizes-two-chimpanzees-as-legal-persons-grants-them-writ-of-habeas-corpus/ |archivedate=2016-09-09}}</ref> 4月21日，刪除保护令中的“人身保护令”（writ of habeas corpus）幾字。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sciencemag.org/sites/default/files/habeas%20update.pdf|title=Judge Barbara Jaffe's amended court order|date=April 21, 2015|website=iapps.courts.state.ny.us|publisher=[[纽约最高法院|New York Supreme Court]]|access-date=April 21, 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150430234057/http://news.sciencemag.org/sites/default/files/habeas%20update.pdf|archivedate=2015-04-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/22/nyregion/judge-orders-hearing-for-2-chimps-said-to-be-unlawfully-detained.html|title=Judge Orders Stony Brook University to Defend Its Custody of 2 Chimps|date=April 21, 2015|website=www.nytimes.com|publisher=[[纽约时报|New York Times]]|access-date=April 21, 2015|archive-date=2021-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411040251/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/22/nyregion/judge-orders-hearing-for-2-chimps-said-to-be-unlawfully-detained.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==支持==
一些有名的支持者诸如灵长类动物学专家[[珍·古德|珍·古德]]，被指派为[[联合国|联合国]]友好大使与[[丛林肉|丛林肉]]贸易作斗争，从而阻止类人猿的灭绝；[[理查德·道金斯|理查德·道金斯]]，原[[牛津大学|牛津大学]]公众理解科学方向的教授；[[彼得·辛格|彼得·辛格]]，[[普林斯顿大学|普林斯顿大学]]哲学系教授；{{le|斯蒂芬·怀斯|Steven Wise}}律师，前哈佛大学教授，{{le|非人类权利计划|Nonhuman Rights Project}}的创始人兼主席，旨在努力推进美国普通法在各州的通过，从而在法律上承认类人猿人格以及其它具有有自我意识且独立自主的非人类动物的人格；他们都主张类人猿具有人格。<ref name=GAPGoodall/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nonhumanrights.org |title=Nonhuman Rights Project |accessdate=2020-09-22 |archive-date=2014-10-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141005201154/http://nonhumanrights.org/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2013年12月，NhRP针对四只黑猩猩被纽约州监禁一例提起了三次诉讼，认为他们应该被视作拥有基本的人身自由权利的法人（即不被囚禁），他们享有普通法赋予的[[人身保護令|人身保护]]权利，因此立即释放并将他们送往保护区。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/27/magazine/the-rights-of-man-and-beast.html?_r=0 |title=Should a Chimp Be Able to Sue Its Owner? |author=Charles Siebert |date=23 April 2014 |publisher=New York Times Magazine |access-date=2015-11-24 |archive-date=2021-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210503203954/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/27/magazine/the-rights-of-man-and-beast.html?_r=0 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 三项人身保护令状的请愿均被否决，保留上诉的权利。NhRP目前正在呼吁三项决议的通过。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Appeals-panel-to-weigh-personhood-for-chimpanzee-5797943.php |title=Appeals panel to weigh personhood for chimpanzee |author=Robert Gavin |date=3 October 2014 |publisher=Times Union |access-date=2015-11-24 |archive-date=2021-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122222607/https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Appeals-panel-to-weigh-personhood-for-chimpanzee-5797943.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>

珍·古德的[[縱向研究|縱向研究]]顯示黑猩猩的社會和家庭行為在某些方面與人類極為相似。她说这些黑猩猩也把她视作家族的一个成员。猿语言能力的实验室研究开始揭示它们的其他人类特征，[[遗传学|遗传学]]方面也得出类似结果，并最终三种类人猿进行了重新归类为[[人科|原始人类]]。

其他如贝兰和埃文斯做的研究<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Beran MJ |author2=Evans TA |title=Maintenance of delay of gratification by four chimpanzees (Pan troglodytes): the effects of delayed reward visibility, experimenter presence, and extended delay intervals |journal=Behavioural Processes |volume=73 |issue=3 |pages=315–24 |year=2006 |pmid=16978800 |doi=10.1016/j.beproc.2006.07.005 |url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16978800 |access-date=2015-11-24 |archive-date=2019-08-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831184636/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16978800 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 表明人类与非人类的灵长类动物在自制力上也有一定相似之处。他们用类似在儿童身上使用的自我分心手段来让黑猩猩控制他们的冲动。类人猿也表现出制定计划的能力，甚至可以“将自己投射到未来”，也就是进行[[心理时间之旅|心理时间之旅]]。故而类人猿似乎也具备自我意识，因为“自我意识实现延迟满足（{{lang|en|delay gratification}}），因为具有自我意识的个体可以推测自己的未来”。<ref>{{Cite journal|url = |title = Animal Cognition: Time Flies When Chimps Are Having Fun.|last =Heilbronner, S. Platt, M., L. |first = |date = 4 December 2007|journal = |accessdate = |doi = 10.1016/j.cub.2007.10.012|pmid = }}</ref>

伴随着日趋严重的类人猿灭绝的风险，[[動物權利|動物權利]]运动向国家施加压力，以承认猿类有限的[[权利|权利]]和法“人”的地位。作为回应，[[英国|英国]]提出了一项禁止使用类人猿进行研究的条例，然而并未对其他灵长类动物做此规定。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://education.guardian.co.uk/businessofresearch/story/0,,1663535,00.html |title=RSPCA outrage as experiments on animals rise to 2.85m |accessdate=2008-06-26 |author=Alok Jha |date=2005-12-05 |publisher=The Guardian |archive-date=2007-03-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070313165826/http://education.guardian.co.uk/businessofresearch/story/0,,1663535,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

作家兼讲师托马斯·罗斯认为给予非人类同等法律权利并不是什么新鲜事。比如多数国家都这样规定：“[[公司法人|公司法人]]是合法的人，享有人类所有的大多数权利，如起诉权，选举权和言论自由。”<ref name="Rose" /> {{le|唐·普林斯-休斯|Dawn Prince-Hughes}}整理了类人猿所满足的人格的标准：“自我意识；对过去、未来、现在的理解；理解复杂的规则和知晓情感带来的后果的能力；选择规避风险的能力，[[同理心|情感共鸣]]的能力，和[[抽象化|抽象思维]]能力。"<ref name="Prince-Hughes138">{{cite book |title= Songs of the Gorilla Nation|last= Prince-Hughes|first= Dawn|authorlink= Dawn Prince-Hughes|coauthors= |year= 1987|publisher= Harmony|location= |isbn=1-4000-5058-8|page= 138|pages= |url= }}</ref>

{{le|格雷·弗兰乔内|Gary Francione}}不认同仅依靠动物是否长的像人类就能判断其是否具备人格，他认为[[感情|感知能力]]才是真正唯一能决定某个物种能否拥有基本权利的因素。因此也应该授予包括小鼠和大鼠在内的其他动物这样的权利。<ref name="Gary 2006">{{Cite journal | last=Francione | first=Gary | title=The Great Ape Project: Not so Great | year=2006 | url=http://www.abolitionistapproach.com/the-great-ape-project-not-so-great/ | accessdate=2010-03-22 | journal= | archive-date=2010-04-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100424035908/http://www.abolitionistapproach.com/the-great-ape-project-not-so-great/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>

==解释==
而根据这些提议或者已通过的声明，类人猿人格合法化可能会给国家或者国际的法律带来保护和义务方面的问题，如： 
* [[世界人权宣言|世界人权宣言]]的7-29项条款 
* 关于人的国籍和公民身份的《[[关于无国籍人地位的公约|关于无国籍人地位的公约]]》和《{{le|1961年减少无国籍状态公约|1961 Convention on the Reduction of Statelessness}}》
* {{le|儿童权利宣言|Declaration of the Rights of the Child}}第四和第五项规定

